269
00:14:10,090 --> 00:14:11,970
I guess I've been pretty tense.

270
00:14:13,120 --> 00:14:14,930
I have to get back to writing soon.

271
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:20,350
And what are you still doing here?

272
00:14:20,350 --> 00:14:22,270
Vroom!

273
00:14:23,740 --> 00:14:25,420
Put down the toy car and listen!

274
00:14:26,130 --> 00:14:27,940
Oh, here it is!

275
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,930
'Scuse us!

276
00:14:31,290 --> 00:14:32,670
You all right, Sensei?

277
00:14:32,670 --> 00:14:34,440
We came to wish you well.

278
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:37,390
You girls came all this way to see me?

279
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:40,230
It's a school day, see.

280
00:14:40,670 --> 00:14:42,770
Our middle school's near here.

281
00:14:42,770 --> 00:14:45,140
Oh, so I'm just a side trip.

282
00:14:45,140 --> 00:14:47,060
That's still nice though, ain't it?

283
00:14:48,580 --> 00:14:51,280
Sensei, your IV's about to run out!

284
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:52,030
What?!

285
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:56,240
Won't it just refill itself
once the bag runs out?

286
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:58,410
It's nothin' that high-tech!

287
00:14:58,760 --> 00:15:00,540
Naru! Use the nurse-call!

288
00:15:00,540 --> 00:15:01,710
Nasu (eggplant)?

289
00:15:02,210 --> 00:15:03,570
There ain't no nasu here!

290
00:15:03,570 --> 00:15:08,840
Nasu! Nasu! Nasu, nasu, nasu!

291
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:06,440
If you don't call Iku-neechan soon,

292
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:08,840
air will get into Sensei's arm and he'll die!

293
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:21,060
Handa Sei
Private Room

294
00:15:10,060 --> 00:15:11,670
But there's no nasu!

295
00:15:11,670 --> 00:15:13,380
The button's right by his pillow!

296
00:15:13,380 --> 00:15:16,850
Pillow-talk! Pillow-talk!

297
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:18,680
Ack, Sensei fainted!

298
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,620
He's spineless!

299
00:15:22,150 --> 00:15:23,900
There was no need to panic.

300
00:15:23,900 --> 00:15:27,270
The recent models won't let air get in.

301
00:15:27,270 --> 00:15:29,450
Oh, yeah? I had no idea!

302
00:15:29,450 --> 00:15:30,780
Give me a break!

303
00:15:31,590 --> 00:15:33,810
I was already in bad shape.

304
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:38,110
Sensei, your temperature has gone up a little.

305
00:15:38,110 --> 00:15:40,400
Shall I insert a suppository to lower it?

306
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:41,490
Suppository?!

307
00:15:41,490 --> 00:15:43,250
Why're you reacting, too?

308
00:15:43,530 --> 00:15:44,560
No!

309
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:46,850
I refuse to engage in humiliation-play!

310
00:15:46,850 --> 00:15:48,740
Humiliation-play?

311
00:15:48,740 --> 00:15:50,470
This is standard medical care.

312
00:15:51,540 --> 00:15:54,510
When that was done to
me back in grade school,

313
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:59,300
I got so embarrassed that I threw up...

314
00:15:59,300 --> 00:16:02,060
You don't need to confess your trauma to me.

315
00:16:02,530 --> 00:16:04,950
We'll keep him under observation for now.

316
00:16:04,950 --> 00:16:08,440
Girls, don't go gettin' him overexcited.

317
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:10,100
Okay!

318
00:16:10,750 --> 00:16:11,670
Huh?

319
00:16:11,670 --> 00:16:12,450
Where's Naru?

320
00:16:13,810 --> 00:16:16,400
What're you doin' down here?

321
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:17,980
Come out of there.

322
00:16:17,980 --> 00:16:19,430
You'll dirty your clothes.

323
00:16:19,430 --> 00:16:20,350
No!

324
00:16:21,180 --> 00:16:23,320
I'll be sure to press it next time.

325
00:16:23,320 --> 00:16:26,630
If anything happens to Sensei,
I'll press the nasu!

326
00:16:26,950 --> 00:16:29,190
Look, the IV's all full now.

327
00:16:29,190 --> 00:16:31,090
Nothing's gonna happen for a while!

328
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:32,430
But...

329
00:16:32,740 --> 00:16:34,090
There's a ghost here...

330
00:16:34,410 --> 00:16:35,820
A ghost?

331
00:16:36,330 --> 00:16:37,680
Grampa told me

332
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:40,790
that there's a ghost in this hospital.

333
00:16:40,790 --> 00:16:42,530
It's scarier'n a monster.

334
00:16:42,530 --> 00:16:43,920
Nobody knows what it is.

335
00:16:44,450 --> 00:16:47,030
Truth is, I'm scared, but...

336
00:16:48,270 --> 00:16:50,530
I wanna see it just once!

337
00:16:51,310 --> 00:16:53,790
Her grampa totally made that up.

338
00:16:55,590 --> 00:16:57,190
What're you doin'?

339
00:16:57,190 --> 00:16:59,050
I'm not listening to you guys.

340
00:16:59,050 --> 00:17:00,830
I don't believe in ghosts.

341
00:17:00,830 --> 00:17:04,190
What'll you do if I hear you talking about
scary stuff and can't sleep tonight?

342
00:17:04,190 --> 00:17:07,240
This hospital is old, so it's really scary!

343
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:08,920
How 'bout a suppository?

344
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:13,670
Why'd you flinch?

345
00:17:14,050 --> 00:17:15,050
'Sup?

346
00:17:15,050 --> 00:17:16,850
I brought the stuff you asked for.

347
00:17:20,510 --> 00:17:21,640
And my writing tools?

348
00:17:21,980 --> 00:17:23,050
No way.

349
00:17:23,050 --> 00:17:24,000
Why not?!

350
00:17:24,430 --> 00:17:25,890
I've been waiting for those!

351
00:17:26,210 --> 00:17:28,710
You just collapsed from overwork!

352
00:17:28,710 --> 00:17:29,840
You need to rest!

353
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:32,750
I'm most relaxed when I'm working!

354
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:34,780
Are you stupid? I'm worried about you!

355
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:35,390
Your eyes are goin' wild!

356
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:36,740
What did you say?!

357
00:17:35,390 --> 00:17:36,740
What's the matter?!

358
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:39,530
Okay, time for us to be headin' home.

359
00:17:39,920 --> 00:17:41,000
Later!

360
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,350
Bye-bye!

361
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,000
Guess I'll go back...

362
00:17:51,290 --> 00:17:52,980
Hello there.

363
00:17:54,170 --> 00:17:56,230
Oh, uh, hello there.

364
00:17:56,230 --> 00:17:57,630
Did I startle you?

365
00:17:58,050 --> 00:17:59,320
Just a little.

366
00:17:59,820 --> 00:18:02,350
I'm in the room next to yours.

367
00:18:02,730 --> 00:18:05,450
Sounded mighty lively in there earlier.

368
00:18:05,450 --> 00:18:07,940
I'm very sorry. Did we bother you?

369
00:18:07,940 --> 00:18:10,060
Oh, no, no.

370
00:18:10,910 --> 00:18:14,000
So, what's ailin' you?

371
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,780
Nothing that bad, really.

372
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,910
Just a summer cold.

373
00:18:18,410 --> 00:18:20,660
Can't be "just a cold."

374
00:18:21,570 --> 00:18:25,180
Weren't they all worried about you?

375
00:18:25,970 --> 00:18:30,580
Those kids seemed mighty relieved
when they heard you were safe.

376
00:18:32,390 --> 00:18:35,960
Please get to feelin' better soon.

377
00:18:51,350 --> 00:18:53,270
HEARTBEAT

378
00:18:55,410 --> 00:18:56,230
Handa-san?!

379
00:18:56,450 --> 00:18:58,150
What are you doing?!

380
00:18:58,150 --> 00:19:01,820
Please tell the Village Chief
to bring me my writing tools!

381
00:19:01,820 --> 00:19:03,600
Your fever hasn't gone down yet!

382
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,380
It's now or never!

383
00:19:05,380 --> 00:19:08,080
I have to write while the idea's still fresh!

384
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:09,410
I'm begging you!

385
00:19:09,410 --> 00:19:10,510
Please let me write!

386
00:19:10,510 --> 00:19:11,790
Come on!

387
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:11,790
No!

388
00:19:11,790 --> 00:19:12,920
I have to write it now!

389
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,200
Stop, Sensei!

390
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:15,120
One moment is everything!

391
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,850
No! You can't, Sensei!

392
00:19:16,850 --> 00:19:19,090
I have a husband!

393
00:19:21,510 --> 00:19:23,510
Sorry 'bout this.

394
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:25,980
I thought you should know.

395
00:19:26,370 --> 00:19:31,140
His fever's gone up from excitement,
so I'll give him a suppository for sleepin'.

396
00:19:37,660 --> 00:19:38,690
Sensei!

397
00:19:38,910 --> 00:19:40,790
You all better now?

398
00:19:40,790 --> 00:19:42,930
Yeah. See for yourself.

399
00:19:42,930 --> 00:19:45,490
Ooh, thank goodness!

400
00:19:45,490 --> 00:19:48,410
Your color does look a lot better.

401
00:19:48,410 --> 00:19:50,110
It's thanks to the sposi-tree!

402
00:19:51,410 --> 00:19:54,600
I'll fill your prescriptions.
Be sure to take them as directed.

403
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:55,910
Why are you so far away?

404
00:19:56,820 --> 00:19:59,440
Don't test my love for my husband!

405
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:00,840
Like I said, why?!

406
00:20:01,690 --> 00:20:04,670
Now to hurry back so I can write!

407
00:20:04,670 --> 00:20:06,730
Oh, you're raring to go, eh?

408
00:20:07,230 --> 00:20:10,730
The old man in the room next to mine
really cheered me up yesterday.

409
00:20:12,970 --> 00:20:14,730
He's in this room... Hm?

410
00:20:18,140 --> 00:20:21,460
Uh, where's the old man who was in this room?

411
00:20:21,460 --> 00:20:22,730
Old man?

412
00:20:23,070 --> 00:20:25,840
You were the only patient here yesterday.

413
00:20:26,290 --> 00:20:29,400
Most folks just go to the new facility.

414
00:20:29,660 --> 00:20:30,370
Huh...

415
00:20:31,450 --> 00:20:34,670
Sensei, did ya see a ghost?

416
00:20:37,760 --> 00:20:40,450
Sensei!

417
00:22:12,290 --> 00:22:13,720
Hello?

418
00:22:14,170 --> 00:22:16,040
I brought meat and potato stew!

419
00:22:18,730 --> 00:22:20,500
What'd you do to your hands?!

420
00:22:21,330 --> 00:22:22,440
Uh, it's nothing!

421
00:22:22,740 --> 00:22:24,100
Nothing at all!

422
00:22:24,100 --> 00:22:25,280
Sensei!

423
00:22:25,770 --> 00:22:29,950
What do I do with these
blood-soaked onions you cut?

424
00:22:30,530 --> 00:22:31,950
That's not blood!

425
00:22:31,950 --> 00:22:35,750
It's a spice! Like Tabasco!
That's what the red stuff is!

426
00:22:36,500 --> 00:22:41,500
Ma, I get the feeling I understand
what you were talking about now.

427
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:45,080
We'll continue to bring
you food from now on.

428
00:22:45,080 --> 00:22:46,720
Huh?! Are you sure?!

429
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:48,630
Ain't that great, Sensei?
